            <h2>대화 기록</h2>
            <div class="chat-box">
                <p><strong>Doctor:</strong> What brings you in today?</p>
                <p><strong>Patient:</strong> I've been having trouble breathing for the past two days.</p>
                <p><strong>Doctor:</strong> I see. Do you feel this happens more when you're <strong>active</strong>, or even while <strong>resting</strong>?</p>
                <p><strong>Patient:</strong> It’s worse when I’m <strong>moving around</strong>, but even <strong>resting</strong> hasn’t helped much.</p>
                <p><strong>Doctor:</strong> Have you experienced any <strong>chest tightness</strong> or <strong>wheezing</strong> along with it?</p>
                <p><strong>Patient:</strong> Yes, my chest feels <strong>tight</strong>, and there’s a slight <strong>wheezing</strong> sound when I breathe.</p>
                <p><strong>Doctor:</strong> Do you have any known <strong>allergies</strong> or a history of <strong>asthma</strong>?</p>
                <p><strong>Patient:</strong> No, I’ve never been diagnosed with asthma, but I do have <strong>seasonal allergies</strong>.</p>
                <p><strong>Doctor:</strong> I understand. Have you noticed anything that might <strong>trigger these symptoms</strong>, like <strong>dust</strong> or <strong>cold air</strong>?</p>
                <p><strong>Patient:</strong> It started after I was outside in the <strong>cold</strong> for a long time.</p>
                <p><strong>Doctor:</strong> That could be a factor. I’d like to <strong>listen to your lungs</strong> and check your <strong>oxygen levels</strong>. After that, we may run some additional tests to rule out <strong>asthma</strong> or other <strong>respiratory issues</strong>.</p>
                <p><strong>Patient:</strong> Alright, thank you.</p>
            </div>
            
                    
